Title: Hamiltonian Flow Equations for a Dirac Particle in an External Potential

Authors: A. B. Bylev, H. J. Pirner

Comments: 6 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B428 (1998) 329-333

We derive and solve the Hamiltonian flow equations for a Dirac particle in anexternal static potential. The method shows a general procedure for the set upof continuous unitary transformations to reduce the Hamiltonian to aquasidiagonal form.